Description: Oval handle sliver of a pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, micaceous, red-brown with white inclusions. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 185, 14? Clay suggests a Cyrenaic provenance; is BA an abbreviation of Barke?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1664)
